However either due to irrational delusions brought upon by wish fulfillment, for the sake of fiction, or having failed basic high school biology - people that want hybrids forgo the finer details and ignore the impossibility.

To put it in simple terms, chromosomes are instructions to create a human and in this case an anthro person. The reproductive cells each contain one half of a chromosome set, like two sides of a zipper. If either half of the zipper pieces from the mother and father do not pass certain checks such as the number of chromosomes that match or drastically different instructions pairings conflict such as a snout vs. a nose, the egg cell will not undergo the division and go on to complete creating a new life.

On the subject of ligers, mules, and other such hybrids. Lions and tigers both share 38 chromosomes, Horses and donkeys are a special case where both have 64 and 62 respectively with mules ending up with 63. So you'd think that "Aha, here's a case where this science falls apart". However that's not the case, the chromosomes contained within horse and donkey DNA matches up until the end. Somewhere along the evolutionary line the last 2 chromosomes that differentiate the two were later revisions. Yet the remaining 62 are practically the same allowing one half of the chromosome zipper to close up and trigger meiosis in the egg.
